

    *** Upgrade python3-setuptools using python-3.10.0 on an existing system with python-3.9.x. ***

step 1:
compile python 3.10.0 --with-ensurepip=yes => pkgmk -d && pkgmk -uf && pkgmk -u

step 2:
compile python-setuptools => pkgmk -d && pkgmk -uf

step 3:
recompile python 3.10.0 --without-ensurepip => pkgmk -d && pkgmk -uf && pkgmk -u

step 4:
newly created python3-setuptools => pkgadd python3-setuptools#version-release

DONE.

Note:

All python modules that reference version 3.9.x will need to be recompiled.


Future rootfs will already have this support, so you don't have to do this operation.
